Reminder: In the original Italian, Baron Julius Evola was simply trying to talk about his grandma's favorite "traditional" pasta recipes, later his writings were misinterpreted and mistranslated as metaphysical/philosophical commentary, similar to 19th century Orientalist poetry.

The "Hermetic Art" is not about Medieval alchemy, but simply a step-by-step guide to preparing authentic Italian spaghetti, "Nigredo" was about adding squid ink pasta, "Rubedo" part of the "Masterwork" is about fresh tomato sauce
